ken in a movie. This facsimile edition of Double Indemnity contains Wilder and Chandler's original -- and quite different -- ending, published here for the first time. Jeffrey Meyers's introduction contextualizes the screenplay, providing hilarious anecdotes about the turbulent collaboration, as well as background information about Wilder and the film's casting and production.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm. 4aGeneral. 4aPerforming Arts. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aChandler, Raymond, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMeyers, Jeffrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilder, Billy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052021848240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092281540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922815423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922815/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles